2
00:00:36,200 --> 00:00:41,804
♪ ♪ ♪

3
00:05:55,653 --> 00:05:59,221
<i>[Peeing]</i>

4
00:06:03,994 --> 00:06:05,894
<i>[Toilet flushes]</i>

5
00:07:25,409 --> 00:07:34,650
♪ ♪ ♪

6
00:08:16,126 --> 00:08:28,070
<i>[Moaning, heavy breathing]</i>

7
00:09:28,065 --> 00:09:41,276
<i>[Moaning]</i>

8
00:10:03,000 --> 00:10:05,300
Sorry, I didn't understand you.

9
00:10:06,604 --> 00:10:08,270
I don't speak French.

10
00:10:08,872 --> 00:10:10,038
Do you speak English?

11
00:10:10,040 --> 00:10:13,308
Yes, a little. Not very good.

12
00:10:14,578 --> 00:10:17,179
That's what every
French person says.

13
00:10:17,181 --> 00:10:18,814
But it's true, no?

14
00:10:18,816 --> 00:10:19,915
No.

15
00:10:21,685 --> 00:10:23,585
Bonne morning.

16
00:10:25,055 --> 00:10:28,523
Good morning.
Do you want to have a shower?

17
00:10:31,629 --> 00:10:35,297
Well, I guess I could use one.

18
00:10:35,299 --> 00:10:37,299
Yes, me too.

19
00:10:37,301 --> 00:10:40,602
<i>[Shower running]</i>

20
00:10:40,604 --> 00:10:43,171
So, where did you do these bruises?

21
00:10:44,441 --> 00:10:49,945
Oh, it's from a movie.
I did a fight scene.

22
00:10:52,516 --> 00:10:55,384
You should be careful with
your home movies,

23
00:10:55,386 --> 00:10:56,752
Mister James Bond.

24
00:10:58,422 --> 00:11:00,055
Where am I, by the way?

25
00:11:00,057 --> 00:11:01,456
Paris.

26
00:11:01,458 --> 00:11:03,558
Yeah, I know that. But where?

27
00:11:05,829 --> 00:11:08,030
Umm, Monmartre.

28
00:11:11,602 --> 00:11:13,702
Uhh, Pigalle.
Do you know Pigalle?

29
00:11:13,704 --> 00:11:14,603
No.

30
00:11:14,605 --> 00:11:15,671
Sacre-Coeur?

31
00:11:16,707 --> 00:11:18,774
Moulin Rouge? Moulin Rouge?

32
00:11:18,776 --> 00:11:19,941
Oh, Moulin Rouge.

33
00:11:21,245 --> 00:11:22,044
Yeah.

34
00:11:22,546 --> 00:11:24,179
That's something I know.

35
00:11:25,315 --> 00:11:27,349
You've heard about Moulin Rouge?

36
00:11:27,351 --> 00:11:28,617
Yeah.

37
00:11:28,619 --> 00:11:30,052
I saw the movie.

38
00:11:32,623 --> 00:11:34,256
It's a place first.

39
00:11:34,258 --> 00:11:36,258
It was a place, before
being a movie.

40
00:11:37,194 --> 00:11:38,326
It's right here.

41
00:11:38,328 --> 00:11:40,495
You can see it from the balcony.

42
00:11:40,497 --> 00:11:41,730
Really?

43
00:11:48,338 --> 00:11:50,238
I think you're clean.

44
00:11:54,411 --> 00:11:55,143
Okay.

45
00:12:12,129 --> 00:12:18,533
I like water. I like air, too.

46
00:12:19,703 --> 00:12:20,802
You like what?

47
00:12:20,804 --> 00:12:22,504
Air, air.

48
00:12:25,109 --> 00:12:30,979
I like elements.
Water, air, wood.

49
00:12:55,472 --> 00:12:57,906
Oh, where are my clothes?

50
00:12:58,675 --> 00:13:00,242
What clothes?

51
00:13:01,378 --> 00:13:03,512
I do hope I had some
on last night.

52
00:13:06,150 --> 00:13:07,582
I'm joking.

53
00:13:08,085 --> 00:13:09,484
I washed them.

54
00:13:11,288 --> 00:13:15,724
They're drying.
They should be dry.

55
00:13:27,471 --> 00:13:29,404
Here. All nice and clean.

56
00:13:42,352 --> 00:13:45,453
And here is everything that
was in the pockets.

57
00:13:45,455 --> 00:13:48,557
Oh, just like in prison.

58
00:13:48,559 --> 00:13:50,125
Excuse me?

59
00:13:50,127 --> 00:13:54,062
Well, I haven't actually been
in a real prison.

60
00:13:54,064 --> 00:13:56,631
Just, you know, in the movies.

61
00:13:56,633 --> 00:13:58,600
Don't worry, I didn't take anything.

62
00:13:58,602 --> 00:14:01,803
I just looked through it to
see if you had

63
00:14:01,805 --> 00:14:03,638
an address, or name.

64
00:14:04,575 --> 00:14:07,876
Yeah, well, I don't carry
anything important

65
00:14:07,878 --> 00:14:09,010
around with me.

66
00:14:09,913 --> 00:14:11,613
I'm losing everything!

67
00:14:13,383 --> 00:14:17,319
Wait - you don't know who I am?

68
00:14:17,321 --> 00:14:19,521
No. You didn't tell me your name.

69
00:14:19,523 --> 00:14:21,656
You were very drunk last night.

70
00:14:21,658 --> 00:14:24,059
You had no identification on you,

71
00:14:24,061 --> 00:14:26,461
and I didn't know where
you were staying,

72
00:14:26,463 --> 00:14:28,830
so I brought you here.

73
00:14:28,832 --> 00:14:31,333
Yeah, I was completely wasted.

74
00:14:31,335 --> 00:14:32,567
Wasted?

75
00:14:33,070 --> 00:14:34,369
Very drunk.

76
00:14:35,305 --> 00:14:38,073
So, what's your name?
Mine is Claude.

77
00:14:38,075 --> 00:14:40,442
My name? Brad.

78
00:14:41,612 --> 00:14:42,611
My name is Brad.

79
00:14:43,180 --> 00:14:44,346
Are you sure?

80
00:14:44,348 --> 00:14:45,046
Yeah.

81
00:14:45,549 --> 00:14:46,948
Nice to meet you, Claude.

82
00:14:46,950 --> 00:14:48,049
Nice to meet...

83
00:14:49,419 --> 00:14:52,654
What? This is how we do it
in France, right?

84
00:14:52,656 --> 00:14:53,989
Yes, of course.

85
00:14:53,991 --> 00:14:56,491
What's this weird accent?
Funny.

86
00:14:57,794 --> 00:15:00,896
My accent?
You find my accent funny?

87
00:15:00,898 --> 00:15:05,033
Yeah, where does it come from?
Arizona, I guess.

88
00:15:06,270 --> 00:15:09,871
Yeah. Let's say Arizona.

89
00:15:09,873 --> 00:15:11,406
Are you in a hurry?

90
00:15:12,876 --> 00:15:16,478
Well - no, actually.

91
00:15:17,180 --> 00:15:20,782
Great! How about some breakfast?

92
00:15:20,784 --> 00:15:22,183
Sounds great.

93
00:15:23,320 --> 00:15:28,890
I think I have some eggs, and
maybe some sausages, too.

94
00:15:28,892 --> 00:15:30,392
Sounds good.

95
00:15:31,161 --> 00:15:32,460
Do you have croissants?

96
00:15:32,462 --> 00:15:34,963
No croissants. Coffee?

97
00:15:35,799 --> 00:15:39,601
Yes, please.
Do you have a cigarette?

98
00:15:39,603 --> 00:15:41,469
No, I don't smoke.

99
00:15:42,673 --> 00:15:44,539
What? You don't smoke,

100
00:15:44,541 --> 00:15:46,508
have sausage and eggs for breakfast

101
00:15:46,510 --> 00:15:48,443
instead of croissants?

102
00:15:48,445 --> 00:15:52,347
What's next, are you going to
tell me you don't drink wine?

103
00:15:52,349 --> 00:15:55,450
No, I don't drink much wine.

104
00:15:55,452 --> 00:15:57,352
Are you sure you're French?

105
00:15:57,354 --> 00:15:59,220
Yeah, of course.

106
00:16:03,026 --> 00:16:04,860
Joking.

107
00:16:04,861 --> 00:16:06,695
And you are American, so what
are you doing here?

108
00:16:06,697 --> 00:16:10,231
Having sex, and smoking, and drinking?

109
00:16:10,233 --> 00:16:12,734
Shouldn't you be shooting a
gun somewhere,

110
00:16:12,736 --> 00:16:14,135
and going to church?

111
00:16:14,137 --> 00:16:16,271
Wow, you do know American well.

112
00:16:16,273 --> 00:16:18,139
Yeah, I lived there for one year.

113
00:16:18,141 --> 00:16:19,240
Oh yeah? When?

114
00:16:20,110 --> 00:16:22,677
It was a long time ago.
I was your age.

115
00:16:22,679 --> 00:16:25,714
I was in Texas. San Antonio.

116
00:16:28,352 --> 00:16:29,250
Why?

117
00:16:31,989 --> 00:16:36,524
I had a love there.
The one true love of my life.

118
00:16:36,526 --> 00:16:38,994
So I moved there to
live with him.

119
00:16:38,996 --> 00:16:41,396
I think that's when I started having

120
00:16:41,398 --> 00:16:43,231
streak and eggs for breakfast.

121
00:16:44,701 --> 00:16:46,568
So what happened?

122
00:16:46,570 --> 00:16:49,704
It just ended.
I moved back to Paris.

123
00:16:49,706 --> 00:16:52,040
I've never gone to
America since then.

124
00:16:53,310 --> 00:16:54,409
That's too bad.

125
00:16:56,313 --> 00:16:57,512
It's okay.

126
00:16:57,514 --> 00:16:59,748
Like I said, it was a long time ago.

127
00:17:01,018 --> 00:17:02,384
It's romantic, though.

128
00:17:03,487 --> 00:17:06,488
Running away to be with
your true love.

129
00:17:06,490 --> 00:17:08,023
It's impractical, though.

130
00:17:09,359 --> 00:17:12,427
I suppose.
I've never been in love.

131
00:17:12,429 --> 00:17:13,728
Never?

132
00:17:13,730 --> 00:17:16,331
No. Not yet, at least.

133
00:17:18,135 --> 00:17:20,268
So what brings you to Paris?

134
00:17:20,270 --> 00:17:24,706
I am... I'm here with my friends.

135
00:17:24,708 --> 00:17:29,444
We came on a college trip.
I'm here for another week.

136
00:17:30,914 --> 00:17:32,947
So it's your first time in Paris?

137
00:17:32,949 --> 00:17:33,948
Yeah.

138
00:17:35,085 --> 00:17:38,319
I was here as a kid, but that
doesn't really count.

139
00:17:38,321 --> 00:17:40,188
What do you think of Paris?

140
00:17:41,324 --> 00:17:42,190
So far?

141
00:17:44,261 --> 00:17:45,660
I love it.

142
00:18:01,244 --> 00:18:03,144
<i>[Knock on door]</i>

143
00:18:04,948 --> 00:18:06,281
Who is that?

144
00:18:06,283 --> 00:18:07,449
I don't know.

145
00:18:13,790 --> 00:18:15,156
It's my friend.

146
00:18:15,892 --> 00:18:17,892
No, no, no!
What are you doing?

147
00:18:17,894 --> 00:18:19,160
Don't answer it!

148
00:18:19,162 --> 00:18:20,361
I have to, it's my friend.

149
00:18:20,363 --> 00:18:22,030
Don't worry, I'll get rid of her.

150
00:19:27,497 --> 00:19:29,864
Goodbye, Mister America!

151
00:19:44,648 --> 00:19:45,914
She's gone.

152
00:19:48,985 --> 00:19:50,818
I should get going.

153
00:19:51,955 --> 00:19:54,889
It's okay, she won't be back.
She's harmless.

154
00:19:54,891 --> 00:19:57,258
A little crazy, but harmless.

155
00:19:57,260 --> 00:19:59,661
No, it's not her. It's just that...

156
00:20:00,697 --> 00:20:02,463
I have to meet my friends.

157
00:20:02,465 --> 00:20:04,332
I don't want to be late and
have them worry.

158
00:20:05,335 --> 00:20:07,235
Finish your breakfast, at least.

159
00:20:13,944 --> 00:20:15,176
Thank you.

160
00:20:18,315 --> 00:20:20,782
Thank you for breakfast, and...

161
00:20:21,751 --> 00:20:23,117
And everything.

162
00:20:26,089 --> 00:20:27,555
I really should run.

163
00:20:32,596 --> 00:20:33,528
Bye.

164
00:20:37,934 --> 00:20:39,500
Are you doing anything later?

165
00:20:40,670 --> 00:20:42,937
No, I don't have plans.

166
00:20:43,907 --> 00:20:46,407
Great! So...

167
00:20:47,244 --> 00:20:49,077
How about dinner?

168
00:20:49,079 --> 00:20:51,479
I could be here by 9ish.

169
00:20:51,481 --> 00:20:53,114
Yes, that could be nice.

170
00:20:53,116 --> 00:20:54,382
- Yeah?
- Yes.

171
00:20:54,384 --> 00:20:55,917
Great. Okay.

172
00:20:56,920 --> 00:21:00,521
Umm, what about my hat?
Do you have it?

173
00:21:04,427 --> 00:21:05,960
Thanks!

174
00:21:07,430 --> 00:21:09,163
What about my sunglasses?

175
00:21:11,735 --> 00:21:15,403
Yeah - I'm very sensitive to the sun.

176
00:21:15,405 --> 00:21:16,671
See you tonight?

177
00:21:16,673 --> 00:21:17,905
Alright.

178
00:22:13,063 --> 00:22:14,362
Hello?

179
00:22:40,490 --> 00:22:49,530
♪ ♪ ♪

180
00:24:58,995 --> 00:25:04,065
♪ ♪ ♪

181
00:26:46,769 --> 00:26:48,336
Thank you!

182
00:26:49,038 --> 00:26:50,237
<i>[Door closes]</i>

183
00:26:55,478 --> 00:27:01,015
♪ ♪ ♪

184
00:28:18,094 --> 00:28:19,994
Catherine...

185
00:28:28,604 --> 00:28:31,939
Aww, baby.

186
00:29:33,102 --> 00:29:33,968
No?

187
00:32:39,922 --> 00:32:47,695
♪ ♪ ♪

188
00:33:49,592 --> 00:33:51,492
<i>[Knocking]</i>

189
00:34:02,104 --> 00:34:04,605
I'm sorry, I don't understand.

190
00:34:05,441 --> 00:34:07,875
Oh, it's you.
The shy American.

191
00:34:08,878 --> 00:34:10,277
You're late.

192
00:34:10,279 --> 00:34:11,145
I know, I...

193
00:34:11,147 --> 00:34:12,346
Shhh!

194
00:34:12,348 --> 00:34:13,747
Come in.

195
00:34:20,456 --> 00:34:22,489
I was just leaving.

196
00:34:22,491 --> 00:34:23,891
Turn around!

197
00:34:31,767 --> 00:34:33,967
Come in, come in, come in...

198
00:34:37,606 --> 00:34:39,239
He's up there.

199
00:34:40,376 --> 00:34:42,276
Don't break his heart.

200
00:36:00,623 --> 00:36:08,629
♪ ♪ ♪

201
00:36:39,261 --> 00:36:40,761
Good morning.

202
00:36:47,403 --> 00:36:48,936
Hung over?

203
00:36:56,645 --> 00:36:58,145
Yes.

204
00:36:59,014 --> 00:37:00,914
It's all your fault.

205
00:37:02,518 --> 00:37:04,318
Where were you?

206
00:37:05,421 --> 00:37:07,321
I'm sorry, I was running late.

207
00:37:08,224 --> 00:37:11,959
My friends... I couldn't get away.

208
00:37:13,429 --> 00:37:15,028
I texted you.

209
00:37:15,030 --> 00:37:17,264
I don't know how to get texts.

210
00:37:18,434 --> 00:37:20,934
Why can't people just call?

211
00:37:23,405 --> 00:37:24,871
You're sparkling.

212
00:37:27,910 --> 00:37:29,176
Oh, yeah.

213
00:37:31,747 --> 00:37:36,750
I was at a stupid party
with my friends.

214
00:37:36,752 --> 00:37:38,952
I couldn't get away.

215
00:37:38,954 --> 00:37:41,588
I'm staying with them.
Where is your phone?

216
00:37:49,932 --> 00:37:51,832
How old is this thing?

217
00:37:53,235 --> 00:37:55,135
It's from the '60s.

218
00:37:55,671 --> 00:37:56,903
It's vintage.

219
00:38:00,709 --> 00:38:04,344
See, here are all the texts I sent.

220
00:38:09,585 --> 00:38:10,617
Uh-huh.

221
00:38:17,226 --> 00:38:20,894
Oh, no! Stay in bed.

222
00:38:25,200 --> 00:38:26,867
Let me take care of you.

223
00:38:28,237 --> 00:38:30,237
Do you want some aspirin?

224
00:38:30,239 --> 00:38:31,405
Yes.

225
00:38:32,007 --> 00:38:35,942
Okay. Breakfast?

226
00:38:42,518 --> 00:38:44,084
Look, I'm sorry.

227
00:38:47,523 --> 00:38:49,156
Let's spend the day together.

228
00:38:50,059 --> 00:38:51,858
I'm free. Are you?

229
00:38:54,563 --> 00:38:56,263
It's Sunday, right?

230
00:38:57,800 --> 00:38:58,899
Yes.

231
00:38:59,768 --> 00:39:02,602
Then yes, I'm free.

232
00:39:11,013 --> 00:39:12,579
This is for you.

233
00:39:16,919 --> 00:39:20,821
I call them the "I'm sorry" flowers.

234
00:39:29,331 --> 00:39:42,809
♪ ♪ ♪

235
00:39:43,912 --> 00:39:47,347
Hey! What are you
doing out of bed?

236
00:39:47,349 --> 00:39:49,983
I'm awake. Do you need help?

237
00:39:55,891 --> 00:39:57,557
This is your aspirin.

238
00:39:57,559 --> 00:39:58,959
Thanks.

239
00:39:58,961 --> 00:40:01,395
But I'm afraid I'm rather
useless in the kitchen.

240
00:40:02,498 --> 00:40:04,398
I can make coffee though.

241
00:40:06,668 --> 00:40:10,537
It's okay - I have these.

242
00:40:10,539 --> 00:40:12,539
Oh, croissants!

243
00:40:12,541 --> 00:40:15,041
Oui oui, you are a French man!

244
00:40:18,347 --> 00:40:28,789
♪ ♪ ♪

245
00:42:11,593 --> 00:42:16,796
♪ ♪ ♪

246
00:42:32,548 --> 00:42:36,416
<i>[Moaning]</i>

247
00:43:44,920 --> 00:43:51,157
<i>[Phone ringing]</i>

248
00:44:05,874 --> 00:44:13,313
No, uh-huh, okay.

249
00:44:28,030 --> 00:44:29,129
Who was that?

250
00:44:29,998 --> 00:44:33,333
My mother, wishing me a
happy birthday.

251
00:44:35,971 --> 00:44:37,537
You're kidding, right?

252
00:44:38,974 --> 00:44:40,707
It's your birthday?

253
00:44:40,709 --> 00:44:41,941
Yes.

254
00:44:43,045 --> 00:44:44,444
No way!

255
00:44:46,381 --> 00:44:48,682
Happy birthday!

256
00:44:48,684 --> 00:44:49,783
Ow, thanks.

257
00:44:51,586 --> 00:44:53,887
Oh, we should do something.

258
00:44:54,856 --> 00:44:57,190
No, I can't. I have to go to work.

259
00:45:00,562 --> 00:45:03,129
I have to go see my friends, too.

260
00:45:03,131 --> 00:45:04,998
I hate birthdays.

261
00:45:07,502 --> 00:45:09,402
We should do something special later.

262
00:45:12,074 --> 00:45:12,906
Okay...

263
00:45:12,908 --> 00:45:14,140
Don't think, don't think!

264
00:45:14,142 --> 00:45:18,478
You can't say no, you can't say no...

265
00:45:18,480 --> 00:45:22,048
<i>[Laughing]</i>

266
00:46:01,990 --> 00:46:08,695
♪ ♪ ♪

267
00:47:59,307 --> 00:48:02,075
So, why did you want to meet here?

268
00:48:03,144 --> 00:48:05,578
This is where we first met.

269
00:48:05,580 --> 00:48:08,181
No - actually, it was over there.

270
00:48:08,183 --> 00:48:09,282
In the gutter.

271
00:48:10,352 --> 00:48:14,821
Oh, well... I was kind of, you know....

272
00:48:14,823 --> 00:48:15,855
Out of it.

273
00:48:15,857 --> 00:48:17,023
A bit.

274
00:48:25,600 --> 00:48:26,733
Let's go to a bar.

275
00:48:26,735 --> 00:48:28,268
No. Enough with bars.

276
00:48:28,270 --> 00:48:30,136
Let's go for a walk.

277
00:48:31,106 --> 00:48:34,040
Your choice! Show me Paris!

278
00:48:34,042 --> 00:48:43,416
♪ ♪ ♪

279
00:49:30,865 --> 00:49:34,767
Why are you shaving?
I like your beard.

280
00:49:34,769 --> 00:49:39,172
Don't worry, it will grow back again.

281
00:49:41,443 --> 00:49:43,910
Don't you think I look younger?

282
00:49:43,912 --> 00:49:45,778
<i>Brad: Well, I</i>
<i>wouldn't say that.</i>

283
00:49:49,718 --> 00:49:51,317
<i>Brad: What about mine?</i>

284
00:49:53,321 --> 00:49:55,421
<i>Brad: Does it make</i>
<i>me look older?</i>

285
00:49:56,591 --> 00:49:57,724
<i>Claude: No.</i>

286
00:49:58,493 --> 00:50:01,694
Shut up, old man!
Happy birthday!

287
00:50:01,696 --> 00:50:04,097
Careful, you're going to
make me cut myself!

288
00:50:05,600 --> 00:50:08,768
<i>Brad: It's okay. I like scars.</i>

289
00:50:09,971 --> 00:50:12,572
<i>Claude: So, you must be</i>
<i>disappointed.</i>

290
00:50:12,574 --> 00:50:14,574
Because my skin is perfect!

291
00:50:14,576 --> 00:50:18,411
Yeah, you think so.

292
00:50:19,280 --> 00:50:23,249
Did you find some
imperfection somewhere?

293
00:50:23,251 --> 00:50:25,618
<i>Brad: No, not at all...</i>

294
00:50:26,388 --> 00:50:28,287
...Elephant Man!

295
00:50:56,851 --> 00:51:04,757
♪ ♪ ♪

296
00:53:15,924 --> 00:53:17,590
<i>[Door unlocks, opens]</i>

297
00:53:59,801 --> 00:54:09,976
♪ ♪ ♪

298
00:55:00,862 --> 00:55:02,361
<i>[Text message tone]</i>

299
00:55:08,369 --> 00:55:11,937
"I am sorry.
Please don't hate me."

300
00:55:11,939 --> 00:55:15,141
"I don't really know
how to explain."

301
00:55:15,143 --> 00:55:17,209
"I'm sure you know
everything now,"

302
00:55:17,211 --> 00:55:19,478
"about who I really am,"

303
00:55:19,480 --> 00:55:24,450
"but the truth is, when I
was Brad, with you,"

304
00:55:24,452 --> 00:55:26,919
"that is who I really am."

305
00:55:26,921 --> 00:55:31,490
"That is the real me, but he
doesn't exist anymore."

306
00:55:31,492 --> 00:55:36,829
"He loved you, but he can
never see you again."

307
00:55:36,831 --> 00:55:38,698
"Love, Brad."

308
00:56:05,693 --> 00:56:07,593
<i>[Crying]</i>

309
00:56:40,962 --> 00:56:42,561
<i>Hello, Claude?</i>

310
00:56:43,464 --> 00:56:44,397
Oui?

311
00:56:44,399 --> 00:56:50,269
Mind if I sit down?
Do you speak English?

312
00:56:50,271 --> 00:56:52,505
Yes, a little.

313
00:56:52,507 --> 00:56:54,240
Great.

314
00:56:54,242 --> 00:56:57,810
My name is Michael.
I'm Aaron...

315
00:56:57,812 --> 00:57:00,112
Um, Brad's manager.

316
00:57:01,182 --> 00:57:06,152
I hate to meet you under these
circumstances, but...

317
00:57:06,154 --> 00:57:07,820
I'm gay myself,

318
00:57:07,822 --> 00:57:10,089
so I understand what
you're going through.

319
00:57:11,359 --> 00:57:16,896
The thing is, um,
Aaron - or Brad...

320
00:57:16,898 --> 00:57:20,466
Signed a contract which had
a morals clause.

321
00:57:20,468 --> 00:57:24,703
And it's a very big film, a
very big part of a franchise,

322
00:57:24,705 --> 00:57:26,705
so, with this morals clause,

323
00:57:26,707 --> 00:57:30,609
if anything were to get out in
the press about him being...

324
00:57:30,611 --> 00:57:33,512
Um, not to the
studio's liking,

325
00:57:33,514 --> 00:57:36,248
and let's just say they're a
very conservative studio,

326
00:57:36,250 --> 00:57:39,485
it could really hurt Brad.
He would be fired.

327
00:57:39,487 --> 00:57:43,155
He could be sued, even.

328
00:57:43,157 --> 00:57:46,192
Because of something like this.

329
00:57:46,194 --> 00:57:49,428
So, I have some form for you.

330
00:57:51,799 --> 00:57:54,733
It's a confidentiality
agreement, there's that,

331
00:57:54,735 --> 00:57:57,970
there's a prepared statement
we've written for you,

332
00:57:59,240 --> 00:58:01,507
which basically states that
nothing happened

333
00:58:01,509 --> 00:58:03,409
between the two of you.

334
00:58:05,646 --> 00:58:08,547
It would be really great if
you could sign these for me.

335
00:58:08,549 --> 00:58:10,316
Um, I have a pen here...

336
00:58:11,185 --> 00:58:17,756
If you could just sign here,
and... here.

337
00:58:18,826 --> 00:58:20,326
Here as well.

338
00:58:22,296 --> 00:58:23,996
And... here.

339
00:58:25,066 --> 00:58:29,935
That would be so... we'd
really appreciate it, so much.

340
00:58:29,937 --> 00:58:32,805
And Aaron really
appreciates this, as well.

341
00:58:32,807 --> 00:58:34,373
I mean, Brad.

342
00:58:34,375 --> 00:58:36,375
<i>[Cell phone ringing]</i>

343
00:58:36,377 --> 00:58:38,644
I'm sorry, I have to get this call.

344
00:58:38,646 --> 00:58:39,945
I hope you don't mind.

345
00:58:43,718 --> 00:58:44,617
Yeah.

346
00:58:47,555 --> 00:58:49,088
Yeah, I'll be there in five minutes.

347
00:58:52,159 --> 00:58:54,193
No, it's not a problem.

348
00:58:54,195 --> 00:58:58,130
Okay, yeah.
Okay, see you in five minutes.

349
00:59:07,942 --> 00:59:10,509
This weather here is just
terrible for my allergies!

350
00:59:14,916 --> 00:59:15,948
Oh.

351
00:59:21,055 --> 00:59:24,523
Oh, make sure to sign
this one, too.

352
00:59:28,829 --> 00:59:30,629
Yes, thank you.

353
00:59:31,399 --> 00:59:33,799
And Brad thanks you, too.

354
00:59:33,801 --> 00:59:38,037
So, um... great.

355
00:59:38,039 --> 00:59:41,407
And we have your contact
information, so...

356
00:59:41,409 --> 00:59:42,975
Here's my card.

357
00:59:43,611 --> 00:59:46,178
Feel free to call me anytime.

358
00:59:46,948 --> 00:59:49,415
I'll be sure to have tickets for you,

359
00:59:49,417 --> 00:59:52,017
for the premiere here in Paris.

360
00:59:52,019 --> 00:59:55,688
And if you're ever in LA,
give me a call.

361
00:59:55,690 --> 01:00:01,226
I'm behind the scenes, so I
have no morals clause.

362
01:00:01,228 --> 01:00:03,395
Okay. Thank you.
Thank you again.

363
01:00:03,397 --> 01:00:05,664
And I'm sorry to bother you.

364
01:00:50,444 --> 01:00:53,545
<i>[Cheering]</i>

365
01:01:00,054 --> 01:01:06,959
<i>[Horror film music,</i>
<i>wolves howling]</i>

366
01:02:23,304 --> 01:02:30,542
<i>♪ Pop music ♪</i>

367
01:02:41,055 --> 01:02:42,955
<i>[Sigh]</i>

368
01:03:14,889 --> 01:03:23,328
♪ ♪ ♪

369
01:04:11,612 --> 01:04:21,687
♪ ♪ ♪

370
01:09:00,934 --> 01:09:02,834
<i>[Knocking]</i>

371
01:09:14,448 --> 01:09:15,714
<i>[Knocking]</i>

372
01:09:24,825 --> 01:09:26,591
Your movie sucked.

373
01:09:28,929 --> 01:09:30,128
I know.

374
01:09:31,932 --> 01:09:34,232
But it's going to make
a lot of money.

375
01:09:38,839 --> 01:09:40,238
Can I come in?

376
01:10:33,594 --> 01:10:35,227
I'm sorry.

377
01:10:40,067 --> 01:10:41,433
Yes, I know.

378
01:10:42,769 --> 01:10:46,838
You are drunk, so you come
crawling back here...

379
01:10:46,840 --> 01:10:50,008
No. I mean, yes, I'm drunk.

380
01:10:52,412 --> 01:10:54,312
But that's not why I came back here.

381
01:10:56,216 --> 01:10:59,951
And why did you come back here, Brad?

382
01:10:59,953 --> 01:11:01,920
Or is it Aaron?

383
01:11:09,263 --> 01:11:11,529
Actually, my real name is Scott.

384
01:11:13,367 --> 01:11:15,267
Scott Aaron.

385
01:11:16,737 --> 01:11:20,238
But I had to change it
to Aaron Davis,

386
01:11:20,240 --> 01:11:23,475
because there was already
as Scott Aaron

387
01:11:23,477 --> 01:11:25,176
in the Screen Actors Guild.

388
01:11:27,814 --> 01:11:28,546
Great!

389
01:11:28,548 --> 01:11:32,284
I'm even more confused now, thanks.

390
01:11:33,453 --> 01:11:45,830
<i>[Cell phone vibrating]</i>

391
01:11:45,832 --> 01:11:47,699
I'm shutting it off.

392
01:11:52,372 --> 01:11:55,040
Cheers, Scott...

393
01:11:55,042 --> 01:11:56,041
Aaron...

394
01:11:56,043 --> 01:11:56,941
Brad.

395
01:12:05,252 --> 01:12:07,152
I came back here for you.

396
01:12:14,494 --> 01:12:16,628
What am I going to do with you?

397
01:12:17,764 --> 01:12:19,631
Whatever you want.

398
01:12:21,101 --> 01:12:27,639
♪ ♪ ♪

399
01:12:34,581 --> 01:12:39,017
<i>[Moaning]</i>

400
01:14:07,541 --> 01:14:09,774
How long are you in Paris for?

401
01:14:11,111 --> 01:14:14,512
I was just here doing press
and publicity for the movie.

402
01:14:14,514 --> 01:14:16,381
My flight is at 8:00 AM.

403
01:14:18,218 --> 01:14:21,052
Oh, I see.

404
01:14:31,665 --> 01:14:33,565
Hey, come to LA with me.

405
01:14:36,536 --> 01:14:38,069
Are you crazy?

406
01:14:38,071 --> 01:14:39,070
Yes, I am.

407
01:14:39,072 --> 01:14:43,041
I can buy your ticket.
You can stay with me.

408
01:14:44,511 --> 01:14:46,644
I don't think so, thanks.

409
01:14:48,114 --> 01:14:52,116
I dropped everything and moved
to the States before.

410
01:14:52,118 --> 01:14:53,685
It didn't work.

411
01:14:53,687 --> 01:14:55,253
Yeah, but that was Texas!

412
01:14:55,956 --> 01:14:57,522
This is LA.

413
01:14:57,524 --> 01:14:59,524
It's still not Paris.

414
01:14:59,526 --> 01:15:02,126
This is where I live, where I belong.

415
01:15:02,128 --> 01:15:04,562
I can't just leave myself behind.

416
01:15:10,103 --> 01:15:12,904
Besides, I don't think your manager...

417
01:15:12,906 --> 01:15:14,639
He's not my manager anymore.

418
01:15:15,475 --> 01:15:17,375
I do what I want from now on.

419
01:15:18,845 --> 01:15:20,044
Until...

420
01:15:30,690 --> 01:15:33,258
It was really nice to see you again.

421
01:15:36,963 --> 01:15:41,232
I think you should get going.

422
01:15:41,234 --> 01:15:43,668
I'm sure you have packing to do.

423
01:15:52,212 --> 01:15:54,345
Can I stay here until my flight?

424
01:15:58,018 --> 01:15:59,984
Yes, I suppose.

425
01:16:02,389 --> 01:16:04,289
What time do you have to leave?

426
01:16:08,461 --> 01:16:10,361
Set the alarm for 5:00 AM.

427
01:16:15,201 --> 01:16:17,468
Yes, it should be.

428
01:16:41,127 --> 01:16:51,235
<i>[Alarm clock ringing]</i>

429
01:16:51,237 --> 01:17:01,245
<i>[Alarm clock ringing]</i>

430
01:17:01,247 --> 01:17:06,551
<i>[Alarm clock ringing]</i>

431
01:17:06,553 --> 01:17:08,286
<i>[Alarm clock stops]</i>

432
